02:14.134 --> 02:15.552
Why is that down there?

02:16.177 --> 02:18.471
- Better safe than sorry.
- Understandable.

02:18.550 --> 02:20.060
Okay, so I've cracked the case.

02:20.120 --> 02:21.980
The money's at the Goodwill. Let's roll.

02:22.010 --> 02:24.561
- What? We can't go now.
- Yeah, Jamal, think about it.

02:24.644 --> 02:28.231
You're right. It's a full
moon, but don't worry, Monse.

02:28.314 --> 02:30.567
- Werewolves don't like dark me.
- It's not the moon.

02:30.850 --> 02:32.600
It's New Years in Freeridge.

02:32.620 --> 02:34.362
Drunk drivers and drunk
people with guns.

02:34.445 --> 02:36.489
No one's hitting up the
Goodwill at this hour.

02:36.573 --> 02:37.573
Good night.

02:38.741 --> 02:41.411
You all suck... and I hate you.

02:43.288 --> 02:44.664
See you tomorrow morning?

02:44.747 --> 02:47.292
0800 hours, don't be late!

02:47.709 --> 02:49.069
You don't need to do this.

02:49.502 --> 02:51.671
It's not safe for you to
be walking home alone.

02:51.754 --> 02:53.882
But it's safe for a 15-year-old
Santo who's been put off

02:53.965 --> 02:55.633
to be sleeping on the streets?

02:55.710 --> 02:57.320
I don't understand why you
couldn't just ask Ruby

02:57.340 --> 02:58.469
or Jamal to crash with them.

02:58.553 --> 03:01.306
Ruby's mom shut me out
when I came to the party.

03:01.389 --> 03:03.016
So why would it be any
different at Jamal's?

03:03.099 --> 03:06.311
- No one needs the risk. Just let it be.
- Let it be?

03:06.686 --> 03:08.605
Seriously? Who do you
think you're talking to?

03:08.688 --> 03:10.857
Just come inside. My
dad's never gonna know.

03:10.940 --> 03:12.859
But I know. And you promised.

03:16.946 --> 03:17.947
I have a workaround.

03:21.910 --> 03:24.037
My dad said you couldn't
stay inside our home,

03:24.120 --> 03:26.164
but he never said
anything about his car.

03:26.247 --> 03:29.667
Monse, house, car, it's
all the same thing.

03:30.251 --> 03:32.545
He doesn't want me around and I get it.

03:32.629 --> 03:34.380
If I were him, I'd feel the same way.

03:35.465 --> 03:37.800
I'll figure something out. Good night.

03:37.884 --> 03:39.260
Don't just "good night" me.

03:42.222 --> 03:43.300
Good night.

03:43.598 --> 03:45.475
I'll see you tomorrow.

03:50.396 --> 03:51.396
I'm leaving it unlocked.

03:52.232 --> 03:53.816
You sure you want to yell that?

03:59.906 --> 04:02.659
Ruby! Mass is in 20 minutes.

04:03.910 --> 04:04.911
I'm not going.

04:05.495 --> 04:06.579
Are you sick?

04:06.663 --> 04:08.373
- No.
- You're in pain.

04:09.165 --> 04:12.043
- Oh, you're constipated again?
- Mom, no!

04:12.126 --> 04:14.170
- I just don't feel like going.
- Oh, you're going.

04:14.254 --> 04:16.464
Why? She's not.

04:17.214 --> 04:18.216
I'm an atheist.

04:18.298 --> 04:20.176
And not part of our family.

04:20.635 --> 04:21.750
Not yet.

04:21.970 --> 04:25.014
Besides, the number one problem
in the world is religion.

04:25.098 --> 04:27.600
That's why Mario and I aren't
gonna baptize the baby.

04:27.684 --> 04:31.145
Get dressed and get in the
car. Everyone's waiting.

04:31.229 --> 04:32.480
Why do I have to swear allegiance

04:32.563 --> 04:34.732
to something that comes out
of a fake country in Italy?

04:36.067 --> 04:38.861
- What happened to you?
- I almost died!

04:39.237 --> 04:41.864
And Olivia did and I just don't
believe if there's a God,

04:41.948 --> 04:43.548
He would let something like that happen.

04:44.826 --> 04:47.495
Okay, okay. You don't have to come.

04:47.578 --> 04:49.247
But I'll see you after for menudo.

04:49.330 --> 04:51.749
Probably not. I got to help Jamal out.

04:53.543 --> 04:54.669
Oh, no, you don't.

04:54.919 --> 04:57.672
If you can't hang with Jesus,
you can't hang with Jamal.

04:58.214 --> 05:00.216
Enjoy your day inside.

05:01.843 --> 05:04.387
I can't believe she's
gonna have my grandchild.

05:07.265 --> 05:08.599
I really like your mom.

